🇬🇧 English Version

`markdown

🧪 Test Output

After building and running the container:
`bash
docker build -t crystalcastle-ai .
docker run crystalcastle-ai
`

You should see output similar to:

`
Epoch 1/5
13/13 [==============================] - 1s 20ms/step - loss: 1.0986 - accuracy: 0.33
Epoch 2/5
13/13 [==============================] - 0s 18ms/step - loss: 1.0950 - accuracy: 0.36
Epoch 3/5
13/13 [==============================] - 0s 17ms/step - loss: 1.0920 - accuracy: 0.38
Epoch 4/5
13/13 [==============================] - 0s 17ms/step - loss: 1.0895 - accuracy: 0.40
Epoch 5/5
13/13 [==============================] - 0s 17ms/step - loss: 1.0870 - accuracy: 0.42

Prediction: [2]
`

- Epoch logs show the training process from model.py  
- Prediction: [2] is the inference result from main.py calling inference.py  
`

